As far as the resulting masses are concerned, we need the size of the operators when

renormalized at a TeV. Strong U(1) effects, and to a lesser extent QCD effects, will cause the
X

various operators to scale differently as they are run down from to a TeV. Generally we expect

that the most enhanced operators will be those with the most subscript 1 fields appearing in

